---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import LessonNav from '../../components/LessonNav.astro';
import LessonAudio from '../../components/LessonAudio.astro';
---
<Layout title="Lesson 4: Team Overview">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <span class="lesson-badge">Lesson 4</span>
    <h1>Team Overview</h1>
    <p class="lesson-subtitle">Hook the judges with a compelling intro to your team and season.</p>
    <LessonAudio slug="lesson-4" />
  </div>

  <p>
    Usually the first section of your portfolio, this is where you hook the judges in. Use this section to give a high-level overview of your season, including:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Awards & Recognitions</strong>: Showcase any awards or special recognitions your team received</li>
    <li><strong>Impact & Growth</strong>: Describe how your team grew and the impact you had on your community</li>
    <li><strong>Team Roles</strong>: Describe the roles and responsibilities of each team member</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This section should also include your team mission, values, and any unique aspects of your team culture. Use visuals to make this section engaging and memorable.
  </p>
  
  <LessonNav 
    prev={{ title: "Best Practices", href: "/lessons/lesson-2/" }}
    next={{ title: "Design Process", href: "/lessons/lesson-3/" }}
  />
</Layout>

